  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Help Lost Boys Support Education &amp; Peace</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In collaboration, three former Lost Boys of Sudan - James Lubo Mijak of North Carolina, Ngor Kur Mayol of Georgia, and James Manyror of Colorado - are working with support of Mothering Across Continents to manage model schools serving home villages. Funds will be used for uniforms, teacher stipends, meals and scholarships at two schools with 300-plus children from three villages. Education and literacy in Unity State rank among the lowest in South Sudan, the world&apos;s most fragile country.</narrative>
  </description>
